Network Policies define how pods are allowed to communicate with each other and with other network endpoints.
Theyâ€™re essentially firewall rules for pods, enforced at the IP level (L3) and port level (L4), using labels and selectors.
You can define policies like:
 â€¢ Only allow traffic from specific pods or namespaces.
 â€¢ Deny all incoming traffic by default.
 â€¢ Allow only certain ports (e.g., port 80 for HTTP).
 â€¢ Restrict egress to the internet or certain IPs.
But remember: Network Policies require a compatible CNI plugin (like Calico, Cilium, or Antrea) to be effective.

